@node "FBN" "A GREAT DLG BBS"
The Fly By Night BBS is a GREAT DLG BBS located here in Portland.  All of the
programs I've ever written (and there are quite a few actually), are being
tested and run on Fly By Night.  All long distance callers will receive a
credit free account.  And FBN is one of the fastest ways of getting in touch
with me!

Just in case you're wondering FBN has an online CD-ROM (currently AmiNet 4),
540 Megs of online file space, and a 16.8k USR modem!  The number is (503)
245-6156, so give it a call, and say hi!
@endnode

@node "GameInfo" "GamesInfo"
This little program is a teaser type of thing for you to put in your login
script.  It's a pretty cool way to attract players to a game.  It will also
automatically detect whether you're running 10,000 and Card Sharks, and
display those games information as well.

To install it, simply put the program somewhere and execute it from your
DLGConfig:Batch/Login.DLGBatch file.  That's all there is to it.
@endnode

